				<td colspan="2"><span>Depends on what your goals are I guess.
<br />

<br />
First of all, bards get hit harder than rangers :P.  If your goal is to level to 65 the fastest, make a bard and just let your wife sponge xp <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.  It's hard to hold aggro as a bard, though I did manage to keep it on Faydedar! /proud
<br />

<br />
If you want to duo in dungeons and such, and not kite all the time.. a Beastlord might be fun. Slow and a pet, plus some decent tanking.  Why, cleric/beastlord might just be more overpowered than a shaman! </span></td>
