			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Old timer needs new Help :)<a name="70728"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 7 04 5:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I also came back to the game just a couple months ago and was looking for a good pair of characters for my wife and I to duo.  We originally began with a Beastlord/Shaman combo but that switched when a RL friend of ours joined and I couldn't keep agro from his rogue as well as I wanted.  So, I remade my BST as a warrior...and the wife and I made a BST and cleric pair and they are pretty brutal.
<br />

<br />
Someone mentioned the BST/Cleric being great for dungeons but I feel like that is one area that they sometimes have a little trouble.  Without a snare (unless she makes a DE cleric), we've occasionally had problems with runners if root breaks at the wrong time.  Also, while it is pretty hard to steal agro from a Beastlord (due to the pet- i've heard of wizards having trouble), the pair will also have a bit of trouble with multiple pulls since one heal can get any extras on the cleric and no taunt is available short of Flash of Light.  However, it is quite possible for the Beastlord to off tank till the pet finishes it's dinner <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I also think the BST would be your best bet because you will level through the lower levels much faster.  Due to the available gear (specifically the weapons), melee characters are able to get much further ahead of the game than the casters.  You get someone to throw a temp on you and you're even better off.  Additionally, your wife will probably get to do a bit more with her cleric than just heal (at least for a while) because the Beastlord is so self sufficient.
<br />

<br />
You might check out www.eqbeastlord.com
<br />

<br />
Because of the ease with which a beastlord can duo with almost any class, half of that board seems to be made up of people asking the best duo or two box for a BST.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
